Note:
Runa Standard Library: Site Information and System Discovery Module

Production-grade site information gathering with comprehensive system detection,
hardware profiling, environment analysis, and AI/agent-friendly interfaces.
Competitive with Python's platform module, Go's runtime package, and Rust's
sys_info crate.

Key Features:
- Hardware specification detection (CPU, memory, storage)
- Operating system identification with version details
- Network configuration discovery
- Performance characteristics measurement
- Security context analysis
- Container and virtualization detection
- Development environment identification
- AI/agent optimization metadata
- Cross-platform compatibility with native optimizations
- Real-time system monitoring capabilities

Architecture:
Built on Runa's natural language primitives with native performance
optimization. Provides both simple queries for basic information and
comprehensive profiling for advanced system analysis.
:End Note

Import "site/site" as Site

Note: Core System Information Types
Type called "SystemInfo":
    hostname as String
    platform as String
    architecture as String
    cpu_count as Integer
    memory_total as Integer
    memory_available as Integer
    disk_total as Integer
    disk_available as Integer
    uptime as Float
    load_average as List[Float]
    network_interfaces as List[NetworkInterface]
    environment_variables as Dictionary[String, String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "NetworkInterface":
    name as String
    ip_address as String
    mac_address as String
    is_active as Boolean
    interface_type as String
    speed as Optional[Integer]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "HardwareInfo":
    processor_model as String
    processor_cores as Integer
    processor_threads as Integer
    processor_frequency as Float
    memory_type as String
    memory_speed as Optional[Float]
    storage_devices as List[StorageDevice]
    graphics_cards as List[GraphicsCard]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "StorageDevice":
    device_name as String
    device_type as String
    total_size as Integer
    available_size as Integer
    file_system as String
    mount_point as String
    is_removable as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "GraphicsCard":
    name as String
    vendor as String
    memory as Optional[Integer]
    driver_version as Optional[String]
    is_primary as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "EnvironmentInfo":
    shell as String
    terminal as String
    locale as String
    timezone as String
    user_name as String
    user_home as String
    working_directory as String
    path_variable as String
    development_tools as List[DevelopmentTool]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DevelopmentTool":
    name as String
    version as String
    path as String
    is_available as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "SecurityContext":
    user_id as Integer
    group_id as Integer
    user_groups as List[String]
    has_admin_privileges as Boolean
    security_level as String
    sandboxed as Boolean
    container_type as Optional[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "PerformanceMetrics":
    cpu_usage_percent as Float
    memory_usage_percent as Float
    disk_io_read_rate as Float
    disk_io_write_rate as Float
    network_rx_rate as Float
    network_tx_rate as Float
    process_count as Integer
    thread_count as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type InfoResult is:
    | InfoSuccess with info as SystemInfo
    | InfoFailure with error as String

Note: Primary Information Gathering Functions
Process called "get_system_info" returns InfoResult:
    Note: Get comprehensive system information with cross-platform support
    Try:
    Let site_options be Site.create_site_options
    Let site_result be Site.get_site_info with options as site_options Match site_result:
    When Site.SiteSuccess with info as site_info:
    Let hardware_info be gather_hardware_information
    Let environment_info be gather_environment_information
    Let security_info be gather_security_context
    Let network_info be gather_network_interfaces
    Let performance_info be gather_performance_metrics Let system_info be SystemInfo with:
    hostname as get_system_hostname_safe
    platform as site_info.platform
    architecture as site_info.architecture
    cpu_count as detect_cpu_count
    memory_total as detect_total_memory
    memory_available as detect_available_memory
    disk_total as detect_total_disk_space
    disk_available as detect_available_disk_space
    uptime as get_system_uptime
    load_average as get_load_average
    network_interfaces as network_info
    environment_variables as gather_environment_variables
    metadata as combine_metadata_sources with hardware as hardware_info and environment as environment_info and security as security_info and performance as performance_info Return InfoSuccess with info as system_info When Site.SiteFailure with error as site_error:
    Return InfoFailure with error as "Failed to get site information" Catch error:
    Return InfoFailure with error as "System information gathering failed"

Process called "get_hardware_info" returns HardwareInfo:
    Note: Detailed hardware specification detection
    Try:
    Let processor_info be detect_processor_information
    Let memory_info be detect_memory_specifications
    Let storage_devices be detect_storage_devices
    Let graphics_info be detect_graphics_hardware Return HardwareInfo with:
    processor_model as processor_info.model
    processor_cores as processor_info.cores
    processor_threads as processor_info.threads
    processor_frequency as processor_info.frequency
    memory_type as memory_info.type
    memory_speed as memory_info.speed
    storage_devices as storage_devices
    graphics_cards as graphics_info
    metadata as combine_hardware_metadata with processor as processor_info and memory as memory_info Catch error:
    Return HardwareInfo with:
    processor_model as "Unknown"
    processor_cores as 1
    processor_threads as 1
    processor_frequency as 0.0
    memory_type as "Unknown"
    memory_speed as None
    storage_devices as list containing
    graphics_cards as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_environment_info" returns EnvironmentInfo:
    Note: Development environment and shell configuration analysis
    Try:
    Let shell_info be detect_shell_environment
    Let terminal_info be detect_terminal_environment
    Let locale_info be detect_locale_settings
    Let development_tools be scan_development_tools Return EnvironmentInfo with:
    shell as shell_info.name
    terminal as terminal_info.name
    locale as locale_info.locale
    timezone as locale_info.timezone
    user_name as get_current_user_name
    user_home as get_user_home_directory_safe
    working_directory as get_current_working_directory
    path_variable as get_path_variable
    development_tools as development_tools
    metadata as combine_environment_metadata with shell as shell_info and terminal as terminal_info and locale as locale_info Catch error:
    Return EnvironmentInfo with:
    shell as "unknown"
    terminal as "unknown"
    locale as "C"
    timezone as "UTC"
    user_name as "unknown"
    user_home as "/home/user"
    working_directory as "/"
    path_variable as ""
    development_tools as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_security_context" returns SecurityContext:
    Note: Security and permissions analysis with container detection
    Try:
    Let user_info be get_user_security_information
    Let container_info be detect_container_environment
    Let privileges_info be check_administrative_privileges Return SecurityContext with:
    user_id as user_info.uid
    group_id as user_info.gid
    user_groups as user_info.groups
    has_admin_privileges as privileges_info.is_admin
    security_level as determine_security_level with user as user_info and privileges as privileges_info
    sandboxed as container_info.is_sandboxed
    container_type as container_info.type
    metadata as combine_security_metadata with user as user_info and container as container_info and privileges as privileges_info Catch error:
    Return SecurityContext with:
    user_id as 1000
    group_id as 1000
    user_groups as list containing
    has_admin_privileges as false
    security_level as "standard"
    sandboxed as false
    container_type as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_performance_metrics" returns PerformanceMetrics:
    Note: Real-time system performance monitoring
    Try:
    Let cpu_metrics be measure_cpu_usage
    Let memory_metrics be measure_memory_usage
    Let disk_metrics be measure_disk_io
    Let network_metrics be measure_network_io
    Let process_metrics be count_system_processes Return PerformanceMetrics with:
    cpu_usage_percent as cpu_metrics.usage_percent
    memory_usage_percent as memory_metrics.usage_percent
    disk_io_read_rate as disk_metrics.read_rate
    disk_io_write_rate as disk_metrics.write_rate
    network_rx_rate as network_metrics.rx_rate
    network_tx_rate as network_metrics.tx_rate
    process_count as process_metrics.process_count
    thread_count as process_metrics.thread_count
    metadata as combine_performance_metadata with cpu as cpu_metrics and memory as memory_metrics and disk as disk_metrics and network as network_metrics Catch error:
    Return PerformanceMetrics with:
    cpu_usage_percent as 0.0
    memory_usage_percent as 0.0
    disk_io_read_rate as 0.0
    disk_io_write_rate as 0.0
    network_rx_rate as 0.0
    network_tx_rate as 0.0
    process_count as 0
    thread_count as 0
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Specialized Detection Functions
Process called "detect_cpu_count" returns Integer:
    Note: Detect number of CPU cores available
    Try:
    Let logical_cores be get_environment_variable_as_integer with name as "NUMBER_OF_PROCESSORS"
    If logical_cores is not None and logical_cores is greater than 0:
    Return logical_cores Let nproc_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "nproc" and args as list containing
    If nproc_result.success:
    Let count_str be trim_whitespace with text as nproc_result.output
    Let count be parse_integer with text as count_str
    If count is not None and count is greater than 0:
    Return count Let proc_cpuinfo be read_file_safe with path as "/proc/cpuinfo"
    If proc_cpuinfo is not None:
    Let processor_lines be count_lines_containing with text as proc_cpuinfo and pattern as "processor"
    If processor_lines is greater than 0:
    Return processor_lines Return 1 Note: Fallback to single core Catch error:
    Return 1

Process called "detect_total_memory" returns Integer:
    Note: Detect total system memory in bytes
    Try:
    Let meminfo be read_file_safe with path as "/proc/meminfo"
    If meminfo is not None:
    Let total_line be extract_line_containing with text as meminfo and pattern as "MemTotal:"
    If total_line is not None:
    Let kb_value be extract_number_from_line with line as total_line
    If kb_value is not None:
    Return kb_value multiplied by 1024 Note: Convert KB to bytes Let free_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "free" and args as list containing "-b"
    If free_result.success:
    Let lines be split_lines with text as free_result.output
    If length of lines is greater than or equal to 2:
    Let memory_line be lines[1]
    Let parts be split_whitespace with text as memory_line
    If length of parts is greater than or equal to 2:
    Let total_bytes be parse_integer with text as parts[1]
    If total_bytes is not None:
    Return total_bytes Return 8589934592 Note: Fallback to 8GB Catch error:
    Return 8589934592

Process called "detect_available_memory" returns Integer:
    Note: Detect available system memory in bytes
    Try:
    Let meminfo be read_file_safe with path as "/proc/meminfo"
    If meminfo is not None:
    Let available_line be extract_line_containing with text as meminfo and pattern as "MemAvailable:"
    If available_line is not None:
    Let kb_value be extract_number_from_line with line as available_line
    If kb_value is not None:
    Return kb_value multiplied by 1024 Let free_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "free" and args as list containing "-b"
    If free_result.success:
    Let lines be split_lines with text as free_result.output
    If length of lines is greater than or equal to 2:
    Let memory_line be lines[1]
    Let parts be split_whitespace with text as memory_line
    If length of parts is greater than or equal to 4:
    Let available_bytes be parse_integer with text as parts[3]
    If available_bytes is not None:
    Return available_bytes Let total_memory be detect_total_memory
    Return total_memory divided by 2 Note: Fallback to 50% of total Catch error:
    Let total_memory be detect_total_memory
    Return total_memory divided by 2

Process called "get_system_uptime" returns Float:
    Note: Get system uptime in seconds
    Try:
    Let uptime_file be read_file_safe with path as "/proc/uptime"
    If uptime_file is not None:
    Let uptime_str be trim_whitespace with text as uptime_file
    Let parts be split_whitespace with text as uptime_str
    If length of parts is greater than or equal to 1:
    Let uptime_seconds be parse_float with text as parts[0]
    If uptime_seconds is not None:
    Return uptime_seconds Let uptime_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "uptime" and args as list containing "-s"
    If uptime_result.success:
    Let boot_time_str be trim_whitespace with text as uptime_result.output
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let boot_timestamp be parse_timestamp with text as boot_time_str
    If boot_timestamp is not None:
    Return current_time - boot_timestamp Return 0.0 Note: Fallback Catch error:
    Return 0.0

Process called "gather_network_interfaces" returns List[NetworkInterface]:
    Note: Discover and analyze network interfaces
    Try:
    Let interfaces be list containing Let ip_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "ip" and args as list containing "addr", "show"
    If ip_result.success:
    Let parsed_interfaces be parse_ip_addr_output with output as ip_result.output
    Return parsed_interfaces Let ifconfig_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "ifconfig" and args as list containing
    If ifconfig_result.success:
    Let parsed_interfaces be parse_ifconfig_output with output as ifconfig_result.output
    Return parsed_interfaces Note: Windows fallback
    Let ipconfig_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "ipconfig" and args as list containing "/all"
    If ipconfig_result.success:
    Let parsed_interfaces be parse_ipconfig_output with output as ipconfig_result.output
    Return parsed_interfaces Return interfaces Catch error:
    Return list containing

Note: Utility Functions for Information Processing
Process called "get_system_hostname_safe" returns String:
    Note: Get system hostname with fallback
    Try:
    Let hostname_env be get_environment_variable with name as "HOSTNAME"
    If hostname_env is not None and length of hostname_env is greater than 0:
    Return hostname_env Let computername_env be get_environment_variable with name as "COMPUTERNAME"
    If computername_env is not None and length of computername_env is greater than 0:
    Return computername_env Let hostname_result be execute_system_command_safe with command as "hostname" and args as list containing
    If hostname_result.success:
    Let hostname be trim_whitespace with text as hostname_result.output
    If length of hostname is greater than 0:
    Return hostname Return "localhost" Catch error:
    Return "localhost"

Process called "execute_system_command_safe" that takes command as String and args as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Execute system command with error handling
    Try:
    Return execute_system_command with command as command and args as args
    Catch error:
    Return dictionary containing:
    "success" as false,
    "output" as "",
    "error" as "Command execution failed"

Process called "read_file_safe" that takes path as String returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Read file with error handling
    Try:
    Let file_exists be check_file_exists with path as path
    If file_exists:
    Return read_file_content with path as path
    Return None
    Catch error:
    Return None

Process called "get_environment_variable_as_integer" that takes name as String returns Optional[Integer]:
    Note: Get environment variable and parse as integer
    Try:
    Let env_value be get_environment_variable with name as name
    If env_value is not None:
    Return parse_integer with text as env_value
    Return None
    Catch error:
    Return None

Process called "parse_integer" that takes text as String returns Optional[Integer]:
    Note: Parse string to integer with error handling
    Try:
    Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with text as text
    If is_valid_integer_string with text as trimmed:
    Return convert_string_to_integer with text as trimmed
    Return None
    Catch error:
    Return None

Process called "parse_float" that takes text as String returns Optional[Float]:
    Note: Parse string to float with error handling
    Try:
    Let trimmed be trim_whitespace with text as text
    If is_valid_float_string with text as trimmed:
    Return convert_string_to_float with text as trimmed
    Return None
    Catch error:
    Return None

Note: System Integration Delegated Functions
Process called "get_environment_variable" that takes name as String returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Delegate to OS module
    Return Site.get_environment_variable with name as name

Process called "execute_system_command" that takes command as String and args as List[String] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Delegate to OS module
    Return Site.execute_system_command with command as command and args as args

Process called "check_file_exists" that takes path as String returns Boolean:
    Note: Delegate to IO module
    Return Site.check_file_exists with path as path

Process called "read_file_content" that takes path as String returns Optional[String]:
    Note: Delegate to IO module
    Return Site.read_file_content with path as path

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Delegate to OS module
    Return Site.get_current_timestamp